Measurement Bias Analysis of EGMA addition at Endline by Treatment Condition in Malawi

PFH & KKN

September 07, 2020

  • Summary
  • Bias Detection Methods
    • Graphical Analysis via Loess
    • Mantel-Haenszel
    • Logistic Regression
    • Item Response Theory

Summary

Dataset: Malawi

Outcome variable: EGMA addition at Endline (add1 - add20)

Comparison variable: Treatment Condition (Control, Tx)

Items with no variance: none

Items with no variance within levels of comparison variable: b add19, add20

Bias detection method: IRT

Total number of biased items: 0 out of 20

Type of item bias: NA

b Items were not included in the IRT-based DIF analysis and were not used to compute IRT-based robustness checks of treatment effects.

No DIF was detected by IRT. Therefore, robustness checks of treatment effects were not performed.
